<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-25-1000 </DOCNO><TEXT>The challenge to system designers is to capitalise on the beneficial contributionsof human operators while guarding against the potential for human error.(All aspects of the plant have to be commensurate with the capabilitiesand the limitations of man). This is considered for the operation ofnuclear power plants. The major areas of system design which challengethe human element are considered - the roles of human operator vis-a-visautomatic systems, the structure of the control room team, display ofplant configuration and performance, facilities for operator interventionand control, decision support systems for operators, concept design andpresentation of operating procedures, design of maintenance and testingtasks, operational management for safety and the regime for initial andrefresher training.</TEXT></DOC>